===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Greek]] [[ιστορία]] (''istoria'') "[[history]]".

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-uk-story.ogg|Audio (UK)}}
*{{audio|en-us-story.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Alternative spellings===
*[[storey]] (''the only spelling used in British English'')

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg-y|stor|y}}

# An [[account]] of [[real]] or [[fictional]] [[event]]s.
#: ''The [[book]] tells the '''story''' of two [[roommate]]s.''
# A [[lie]].
#: ''You’ve been telling '''stories''' again, haven’t you?''
# A [[floor]] or [[level]] of a [[building]].
#: ''Our [[shop]] was on the fourth '''story''' of the building &mdash; we had to install an [[elevator]].''

====Synonyms====
* (''1'') [[tome]]
* (''2'') ''See [[lie]]''
* (''3'') [[floor]], [[level]]

